      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SASSY GALLEON (3) made it four wins from her past five starts here when she came from a back row draw to score last start. That was more than five weeks ago but she has been kept up to the the mark with a trial. Galloped out the last time she attempted a standing start so she'll need to get it right but she owns a 50 per cent strike rate at this distance. GOLDEN SUNSET (7) had her run of top-four finishes come to an end when she raced parked and faded last week but she came from this mark to place the last time she tackled a standing start race. KODA DA MODA (2) is going well, winning from 30m two back before a second from the back row last start. Suited off the front mark. The best form of SHEZA CHANCE (4) would measure up here.",
